		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Totally flat. I think the socket that comes with copyNES is specialized. That not 100% statement is almost definitely (and unfortunately) not true.
<br />
<br />I bought some strip sockets to try and fix the problem with: 
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://alpha.octopart.com/Mill-Max__310-93-120-41-001__0.jpg">http://alpha.octopart.com/Mill-Max__310 ... 001__0.jpg</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />My plan is to attach the strip sockets to the male end on the copyNEs board, and then bend the pins to fit on the NES board.

		

